  "prompt": "Which app should I use to locate lost or stolen phone even after a factory reset is performed? My phone is rooted.",
  "response": "To locate a lost or stolen phone, especially one that has been rooted and might undergo a factory reset, you'll want an app that can survive such drastic measures. One of the best options for this scenario is **Cerberus**.\n\nHere's why Cerberus is a good choice:\n\n1. **Survives Factory Reset**: Cerberus can be installed in a way that it survives factory resets. This is done by integrating it into the system partition, which is not affected by a standard factory reset.\n\n2. **Root Access**: Since your phone is rooted, you can take full advantage of Cerberus's advanced features. Root access allows Cerberus to hide its icon and operate covertly.\n\n3. **Comprehensive Features**: Cerberus offers a wide range of features including remote locking, wiping data, taking pictures, recording audio, and even displaying a message on the lost device.\n\n4. **Multiple Activation Methods**: You can activate Cerberus via SMS, through the web, or using Google's Find My Device.\n\nTo set up Cerberus on your rooted device:\n\n1. **Install Cerberus**: Download and install the Cerberus app from the Google Play Store or their official website.\n\n2. **Activate Root Features**: Open the app, go to settings, and enable root features. This will allow Cerberus to hide its icon and survive a factory reset.\n\n3. **Integrate into System Partition**: Use the option to install Cerberus into the system partition. This step requires root access and will ensure that Cerberus survives a factory reset.\n\n4. **Set Up Account**: Create an account on the Cerberus website and link your device to it. This will allow you to control your device remotely.\n\n5. **Test**: Make sure to test the functionality to ensure everything is set up correctly.\n\nBy using Cerberus, you increase your chances of locating your device even if it's reset to factory settings. Always remember to keep your device's location services enabled and to have a strong password or biometric lock to prevent unauthorized access to your device's settings.",
